         ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^     ^^^^^^
	- AmigaOS 3.x (kickstart V39 or V40)
	
	- Versions for 68000, 68020 and 68020+fpu are available
	  (extra heavy optimized versions also available, but I
	   don't trust optimizers at all)

@endnode

@node "MacWB.inst" "Installing Instructions"
@smartwrap
@{jcenter}@{line}@{b}Installing to the system@{ub}
@{par}@{jleft}

First, there is no installer script as you should not just click
and install this program without thought.@{LINE}

MacWB consists only of one executable binary. Copy it to a location
in your path, I suggest C: is a good place for it. If you want to
use it permanently, edit your S:USER-STARTUP file and add this lines:@{LINE}
@{code}
	;BEGIN MacWB hack
	run <>NIL: MacWB
	;END MacWB hack@{line}
@{pard}
There is a font included in this archive, YOU NEED this font or MacWB will
refuse to work. Just copy the contents of the "fonts/" drawer to one of your
FONTS: location. Read on @{"here" link the.font} about the font!@{par}@{line}
@{jcenter}@{b}Removing from the system@{ub}@{par}@{jleft}
@{pard}
Just delete the binary and remove the S:USER-STARTUP entry, then reboot. It is possible
to remove the hack from the system while its running: Just install PatchControl or
SetMan and signal a CTRL-C to the program. @{B}WARNING!@{UB} YOU HAVE TO CLOSE ALL WINDOWS
USING MAC-GADGETS BEFORE OR YOUR SYSTEM *WILL* CRASH! Removing a patch from the
system is not a wise decision - better delete its invocation and reboot.
@endnode

@node "MacWB.conf" "Configuration"
@{jcenter}@{line}@{b}Preparing your system for the use with MacWB@{ub}
@{par}@{jleft}@{line}
MacWB is a hack and does not like to interfere with other hacks. Check
the following list and try to fix all this topics before using MacWB:
@{code}@{line}
	MacWB does not like slider patches for the Workbench:

	- If you are using MCP you have to switch off the "SysIHack/Props" (MCP V1.11)
	
	- I'm sure sysihack/urouhack etc. will confuse MacWB. Please tell me!
	  I haven't tested it...

	- MacWB should be the last hack of Intuition hacks
	
	- MacWB DOES NOT WORK TOGETHER WITH WORKBENCH 95 !!!!!!
	
	- Because it is possible to start MacWB twice or more you should
	  avoid this.
	
	- Read the BUGS section

@endnode

@node "MacWB.gads" "Gadgets and Windows"
@{line}
@{jcenter}@{b}How this art gallery works@{ub}@{par}@{jleft}
@{pard}@{line}
@smartwrap
Each button starts a @{fg shine}MultiView@{fg text} utility with a picture. You should
have @{fg shine}MultiView@{fg text} in SYS:utilities or you won't see anything. All launched @{fg shine}MultiView@{fg text}'s
are new processes, so you can launch as many as you may want to launch.
(You have to close all these @{fg shine}MultiView@{fg text}'s manually).

@{LINE}@{code}@{jcenter}@{b}Have a look at the "original"@{ub}@{par}@{jleft}
@{pard}
@smartwrap
The pictures A to C are showing snapshots of an original macintosh environment. Picture A
is showing an activated window with scaled sliders. Have a look at the top placed titlebar:
you see a centered title, the small rectangle to the left is the CLOSE gadget and the gadget
in the opposite direction is for ZOOMing the window. The whole striped area of the titlebar
is known as the dragbar; click into it and move the mouse to drag the window. The window is
active; this means it has high detail rendering. Just compare it to picture C! The small
gadget in the lower right corner is known as the SIZE gadget.
@{par}@{code}
	@{" A " system "run <>NIL: sys:utilities/multiview pics/mac.active.sliders"} An active Macintosh window with sliders
	@{" B " system "run <>NIL: sys:utilities/multiview pics/mac.active.nosliders"} An active Macintosh window without sliders
	@{" C " system "run <>NIL: sys:utilities/multiview pics/mac.inactive"} An inactive Macintosh window (gadgets aren't rendered)

@{jcenter}@{b}Now some impressions of what it looks like"@{ub}@{par}@{jleft}
@{pard}
@smartwrap
And now your first looks to the amiga versions. Note that the sliders are not ready yet
and that not everything matches exactly the macintosh original! MacWB removes the arrow
gadgets, this is not a bug. The sliders also are getting 'pumped', so they are a bit bigger
than the original (the mac has fat sliders, too).
@{par}@{code}
	@{" D " system "run <>NIL: sys:utilities/multiview pics/win.rename.active"} The Workbench RENAME dialog box (active)
	@{" E " system "run <>NIL: sys:utilities/multiview pics/win.rename.inactive"} The Workbench RENAME dialog box (inactive)
	@{" F " system "run <>NIL: sys:utilities/multiview pics/win.execute.active"} The Workbench EXECUTE dialog box (active)
	@{" G " system "run <>NIL: sys:utilities/multiview pics/win.execute.inactive"} The Workbench EXECUTE dialog box (inactive)
	@{" H " system "run <>NIL: sys:utilities/multiview pics/win.ramdisk.active"} An active Workbench window with full sliders
	@{" I " system "run <>NIL: sys:utilities/multiview pics/win.ramdisk.inactive"} An inactive Workbench window with full sliders
	@{" J " system "run <>NIL: sys:utilities/multiview pics/win.modules.active"} An active Workbench window with scaled sliders
	@{" K " system "run <>NIL: sys:utilities/multiview pics/win.data.inactive"} An inactive Workbench window with scaled sliders

@{jcenter}@{b}Some additional information pictures@{ub}@{par}@{jleft}
@{pard}
@smartwrap
The following pictures are showing miscellaneous features or bugs I've encountered.
This list will grow in the future (not the number of bugs, the number of pictures! :-)
@{par}@{code}
	@{" L " system "run <>NIL: sys:utilities/multiview pics/win.delete.bug"} The Workbench DELETE dialog box (using RTPatch)
	@{" M " system "run <>NIL: sys:utilities/multiview pics/win.shifter"} This was the hidden patch (removed)
@endnode

@node "MacWB.tech" "Technical Informations"
@{jcenter}@{line}@{b}Technical Informations@{ub}
@{par}@{jleft}

Several patches to intuition gadgets are available. They all patch the sysiclass,
intuitions image generator. Instead of let sysiclass create the images,
the patches create them.@{par}@{line}

I'm patching the OpenWindowTags() function of Intuition
and comparing the taskname to "Workbench". If and only if the calling task
is the Workbench, I'll start scanning the parameters and start changing it
a little bit. The new gadgets are private BOOPSI classes; the old gadgets
were intercepted. After deleting/filtering the parameters I call the original
function and AddGadget() the BOOPSI objects to the window (I could use the
WA_Gadgets tag for this). All additional data is stored in a special memory
node which is linked to the window's RastPort->RP_User. Extensive checkings
and experiments to a possible O(1) location ended in this pointer (for the
first).The sliders are getting pumped, arrow gadgets being removed, and so
on.@{par}@{line}

However, it is not very clever to assume undocumented things. But
since the Amiga is dead (officially :-) we could not expect a new version
of intuition.library and so for now its behaviour is deterministic.@{par}
@endnode

@node "MacWB.dev" "Developer Informations"
@{jcenter}@{line}@{b}Developer Informations@{ub}
@{par}@{jleft}

I've included the sourcecode in this archive, mainly for debugging reasons.
Please tell me what you think and what should be changed.
@{par}
I'm also searching for some guys writing me some BOOPSI classes for custom
gadgets, in other words:@{line}
@{code}
	- send me code that draws a nice image (search for IM_DRAW in the code)
	
	- send me pictures with nice ideas of a future amiga OS
	  (try to put the pictures onto a web page and send me the links, please)
	
	- send me QUICK filling routines. I'm searching for some LR-gradient code,
	  that could fill a rectangle with a LR-gradient using a supplied set of
	  pens (I want to fill the titlebar with gradients...)

	- more ideas...

@smartwrap
As this hack should be general enough to change the workbench windows to each
possible style, it would be nice to think about an external module system for
different kind of styles..

@endnode

@node "MacWB.bugs" "Bugs"
@{jcenter}@{line}@{b}Hard weighted bugs@{ub}
@{par}@{jleft}
@{code}
	- if the WB screen has an incorrect ratio (like WB in "Lores")
	  the prop sliders are mangled

	- the "secret patch" made the patched software unusable :-(

@smartwrap
@{jcenter}@{line}@{b}Soft weighted bugs@{ub}@{par}@{jleft} @{code}
	- sometimes the CLOSE/ZOOM gadget aren't refreshed
	  (just reactivate the window)
	
	- the old window title sometimes flickers through the
	  gadgets (intuition tries to render the title :-(

	- EasyRequestArgs requesters (DELETE, COPY-REPLACE, ..)
	  have cosmetical errors.

	- reqtools requester look ugly (not my fault...)

@smartwrap
@endnode

